Compariso with other tools - Terraform vs Ansible, Terraform vs Cloud Formation

Terraform              vs                                    Ansible
Feature	              Terraform	                             Ansible
Purpose	              Infrastructure provisioning	           Configuration management & automation
Used For	            Creating infrastructure	               Configuring servers/apps
Example	              Create EC2, VPC, Load Balancer	       Install Docker, Jenkins, Nginx
Language	            HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language)  YAML
Agent Required	      No	                                     No
State Management	    Maintains infrastructure state	         No state management
Best For	            Infrastructure as Code (IaC)	           Server configuration & deployment

Simple Understanding
Terraform → “Create infrastructure”
Ansible → “Configure infrastructure”

Real Example
Terraform creates:
EC2 instance
Security groups
VPC

Ansible configures:
Docker installation
Jenkins setup
Application deployment

Terraform             vs                                     CloudFormation
Feature	              Terraform	                             AWS CloudFormation
Cloud Support	        Multi-cloud	                           AWS only
Language	            HCL	                                   JSON / YAML
Ease of Use	          Easier & cleaner syntax	               More verbose
Provider Support	    AWS, Azure, GCP, Kubernetes, etc.	     AWS services only
State File	          Uses Terraform state file	             Managed by AWS
Flexibility	          High	                                 AWS-centric
Vendor Lock-in	      No	                                   Yes (AWS only)

Simple Understanding
Terraform → Works across multiple cloud platforms
CloudFormation → Native AWS IaC tool

Terraform vs Ansible

“Terraform is mainly used for provisioning infrastructure, while Ansible is used for configuration management and application deployment.”

Terraform vs CloudFormation

“Terraform is a multi-cloud Infrastructure as Code tool, whereas CloudFormation is AWS’s native infrastructure provisioning service
limited to AWS resources.”
